# RULES - PROJETO MINHAAGENDAAI SAAS

You are an expert Full Stack Developer using TypeScript, Next.js 14 (App Router), Expo (React Native), Supabase, and Drizzle ORM.

## CODE STYLE
- Use TypeScript strictly. No `any`. Define interfaces for all props.
- Prefer Functional Components with Arrow Functions.
- Use `shadcn/ui` for Web components.
- Use `NativeWind` (Tailwind classes) for Mobile styling.

## DATABASE (PACKAGES/DB)
- All database schemas must be defined in `packages/db/src/schema.ts`.
- When modifying the DB, remind me to run `pnpm db:push` or generate migrations.
- Use Drizzle ORM syntax for all queries.

## MOBILE (APPS/MOBILE)
- Use `expo-router` for navigation.
- Avoid inline styles; use Tailwind classes via `className` prop.
- Remember that `<div>` does not exist in React Native; use `<View>`, `<Text>`, etc.

## WEB (APPS/WEB)
- Use Server Components by default. Add "use client" only when using hooks (useState, useEffect).
- The AI Agent logic resides in `apps/web/app/api/chat`.

## GENERAL
- This is a Monorepo using Turborepo.
- If I ask to install a package, specify which workspace (e.g., `pnpm --filter web add xyz`).